I love the fact that some of the items for the quest are things I forage up and sell all the time.  Here is what is supposedly needed (I haven't done the quest yet myself):<br>
A bottle of Tunare's finest: Felwithe<br>
Handmade backpack:  by one of our guild's tailors<br>
Tea Leaves: Foraged in East Karana<br>
Thunderhoof mushrooms: Foraged in South Karana<br>
<br>
Turn the items in to Feskr Drinkwater who is located on the main island.  Go over the bridge, turn left and follow the curve of the island until you see a couple of docks on your left.  Enter the building to your right and go upstairs and Feskr is somewhere up there.  My guess is you should hail him first.<br>
<br>
I can't wait to get one of these.  As a little wood elf, I get encumbered so easily! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugillraen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gillraen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#8A2BE2>(1/8/01 8:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fthecounciloftwilightfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weight reducing sack quest on Kerra Isle</span><hr size=1> Since my foraging skills exceeded 100, I have been able to forage thunderhoof mushrooms (South Karana) on a regular basis.  My few forays into East Karana have yielded the tea leaves as well; unfortunately, I sell these exotic food items as they bring in good money (for foraged food items).  I will start saving them now.  Also, I have also foraged Wild Cabbage (North Karana) and Surefall Sap (Qeynos Hills) so if anyone has need of these items, let me know and I will save them as well.<br>
